<p><b>Hellboy</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Fictional_character" title="Fictional character" class="mw-redirect">fictional character</a>, created by writer-artist <a href="/wiki/Mike_Mignola" title="Mike Mignola">Mike Mignola</a>. He has appeared in a number of <a href="/wiki/Eponym" title="Eponym">eponymous</a> <a href="/wiki/Limited_series" title="Limited series">miniseries</a> and <a href="/wiki/One-shot_(comics)" title="One-shot (comics)">one-shots</a>, as well as some <a href="/wiki/Intercompany_crossover" title="Intercompany crossover">crossovers</a>.</p>
<p>The character Hellboy is a <a href="/wiki/Demon" title="Demon">demon</a> who fights for the <a href="/wiki/U.S._government" title="U.S. government" class="mw-redirect">U.S. government</a> and himself against dark forces including <a href="/wiki/Nazism" title="Nazism">Nazis</a> and <a href="/wiki/Baba_Yaga" title="Baba Yaga">Baba Yaga</a>, in a series of tales that have their roots in <a href="/wiki/Folklore" title="Folklore">folklore</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pulp_magazine" title="Pulp magazine">pulp magazines</a>, vintage adventure, and <a href="/wiki/Horror_fiction" title="Horror fiction">horror fiction</a>.</p>
<p>The comics were adapted into <a href="/wiki/Hellboy_(film)" title="Hellboy (film)">a 2004 film</a> starring <a href="/wiki/Ron_Perlman" title="Ron Perlman">Ron Perlman</a>, a 2008 film sequel, <i><a href="/wiki/Hellboy_II:_The_Golden_Army" title="Hellboy II: The Golden Army">Hellboy II: The Golden Army</a></i>, and two <a href="/wiki/Hellboy_Animated" title="Hellboy Animated">straight-to-DVD animated films</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Hellboy:_Sword_of_Storms" title="Hellboy: Sword of Storms">Hellboy: Sword of Storms</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Hellboy:_Blood_and_Iron" title="Hellboy: Blood and Iron">Hellboy: Blood and Iron</a></i>.</p>
